\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 47. C. affinis} Schultes in Roemer & Schultes, {\i Syst. Veg.} {\b 5}: 140 (1819). Biennial. Stem simple, erect, rather robust, setose-hispid, leafy. Leaves 10-15 cm, linear-lanceolate, subglabrous above, with setose-ciliate margin; basal attenuate at the base, sessile; cauline sessile, sometimes semiamplexicaul. Flowers violet, axillary and terminal. Pedicels setose-hispid. Calyx-teeth half as long as corolla; appendages deflexed, as long as the teeth and ovary. Corolla 20-40 mm, broadly campanulate; lobes rather short. • {\i Mountains of E. Spain. }Hs.
