\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 48. C. formanekiana} Degen & Dörfler,{\i  Denkschr. Akad. Wiss. Math.-Nat. Kl.} ({\i Wien}) {\b 54}: 728 (1899). More or less pubescent biennial. Stem 10-20 cm, erect, branched from the base. Leaves with winged, dentate petiole; basal ovate-spathulate, crenate-dentate; cauline spathulate. Flowers terminal. Calyx-teeth triangular-ovate, denticulate, 3 times as long as the ovary. Corolla 50-60 mm, broadly campanulate, white or blue-lilac, sparsely pubescent outside, glabrous inside. 2n = 24.{\i  Rock-crevices. • Macedonia.} Gr Ju.
