\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 49. C. lingulata} Waldst. & Kit.,{\i  Pl. Rar. Hung. }{\b 1}: 65 (1801). Hispid biennial. Stems 1 to numerous, 20-30 cm, simple. Basal leaves crenate-serrate, oblong-spathulate, narrowed at the base, petiolate; upper oblong to lanceolate, crenate-serrate, sessile. Inflorescence capitate, terminal, sometimes with some axillary clusters, with lanceolate involucral leaves. Flowers sessile. Calyx-teeth oblong, obtuse; appendages ovate, longer than the ovary. Corolla 20-25 mm, tubular-infundibuliform, violet. 2n = 34.{\i  Grassy places and scrub. • Balkan peninsula, S.W. Romania; S. Italy.} Al Bu Gr It Ju Rm Tu.
